Decorator Design Pattern :
⦁	It is one of the structural design pattern.
⦁	It allows us to dynamically add functionality and behaviour to an object without affecting the behaviour of other objects within the same class. 

Advantages : 
⦁	Decorator design pattern is useful in providing runtime modification abilities and hence more flexible. 
⦁	It’s easy to maintain and extend when the amount of choices are more.

Disadvantages :  
⦁	 It uses plenty of similar kind of objects (decorators).
